OL,6,FSpeaking on behalf of the prosecution,
OL,7,FSarah Gaunt, who read out dozens of
OL,8,Fmessages, said she wanted to give the
OL,9,Fjury a sense of the "magnitude" and
OL,10,Ftypes of communications being sent.
OL,12,FShe explained the messages had been
OL,13,Fdownloaded from phones either seized
OL,14,Ffrom the defendants or that had been
OL,15,Fin "close proximity" to them.
OL,17,FIn one call captured by the police in
OL,18,FShamo's car, he asked an "Uncle Andam"
OL,19,Fif he had people in Croatia or Italy
OL,20,Fthat he could smuggle.
